# Chat Page (Two-State UI)

The chat page (`/`) has two states toggled by JS. Served via `app.main.read_root` -> `chat.html`.

**Theme tokens live in** `app/static/css/app.css` and are documented in `../ui.mdc`. All chat colors use existing CSS custom properties only.

## State A: Landing

Centered hero with prompt input. Visible on initial page load.

- **Container:** `#landing.hero-container` — centered column, `max-width: 600px`.
- **Title:** `<h1 class="app-name">Monitor <kbd>Power</kbd> .</h1>`
- **Input Area:** `.input-area`
  - `textarea#landing-input` — `min-height: 100px`, `border-radius: 12px`, no resize.
  - `.input-meta` — flex row with model `<select#landing-model>` (left) and `<small>` helper text (right).
- **Send trigger:** Enter key only (no send button). Shift+Enter for newline.

## State B: Chat

iMessage-style bubble layout. Shown after first message via JS class toggle.

- **Transition:** JS hides `#landing`, removes `hidden` from `#chat`, adds `.chat-active` to `<main>`.
- **`main.chat-active`** overrides: `justify-content: flex-start; padding: 0`.
- **Container:** `#chat.chat-container` — flex column, `max-width: 720px`, full height.

### Messages (`.chat-messages`)

- Flex column, `overflow-y: auto`, `gap: 0.5rem`.
- Each message: `.bubble-row` > `.bubble` (created by JS).
- `.bubble-row.user` — `justify-content: flex-end`.
- `.bubble-row.assistant` — `justify-content: flex-start`.
- `.bubble` — `max-width: 75%`, `border-radius: 18px`, flat colors, no gradients.
  - `.bubble.user` — `--pico-primary-background` bg, `--pico-primary-inverse` text, tail bottom-right (`4px`).
  - `.bubble.assistant` — `--pico-card-background-color` bg, `--pico-base-color` text, `--pico-muted-border-color` border, tail bottom-left (`4px`).

### Input Bar (`.chat-input-bar`)

- Pinned to bottom. `--pico-card-background-color` bg, top border `--pico-muted-border-color`.
- `.model-pill` — compact `<select>`, `font-size: 0.7rem`, transparent bg, muted border, `border-radius: 12px`.
- `.input-row` — flex row: `textarea#chat-input` (flex: 1, `border-radius: 18px`) + `.send-btn` (40px circle, `--pico-primary-background`).

## Model Selection

- Models fetched from `GET /api/models` on page load (returns `[{id, name}]`).
- Populates both `#landing-model` and `#chat-model` selects.
- On state transition, chat model syncs from landing model value.

## Cross-Browser

- All custom `<select>` and `<button>` elements use `-webkit-appearance: none; appearance: none`.
- Flex children use `min-width: 0; width: auto` to prevent Pico's `width: 100%` from breaking layout.
- State transition uses `.chat-active` class on `<main>` (no `:has()` selectors).

